identifications.body: "Common Yarrow Species Complex" is not incorrect, but the native North American plants can be distinguised more precisely (and distinguished from introduced European A. millefolium s.s.) as "borealis". As far as I am aware, introduced A. millefolium s.s. has not been documented as a wild plant in the Pacific Northwest.
